The President and Chief Executive Officer of Cooperatives Rating and Award Society of  Nigeria (CRASON),  Victor Oyegoke has stressed the need for Government to collaborate with Cooperative societies as key players in the diversification move. Oyegoke said that the Next Level Government of President Muhammadu Buhari needs to reach out and collaborate with the Cooperative sector with a view to diversifying the nation’s economy. He said, “I am seizing this opportunity to call on government to see the need bring from the Cooperative sector a key person into the Economic Council Team of the Federal Government,” he said. Addressing newsmen in Lagos ahead of the 2nd National Cooperative Awards, Symposium and Exhibition slated for this week in Abuja, Oyegoke said more than 1,000 key decision makers in cooperatives are expected to attend. The event themed ‘Strengthening Cooperatives to serve as Catalyst for Nigeria’s Socio- Economic Development of our Nation’, he said will have experts discuss topics including: ‘Cooperatives and the Use of Technology’, ‘Leadership, Advocacy, Entrepreneurship skills’ and ‘Fund Raising Strategies for Cooperatives’ among others. He further described the Nigerian National Cooperative Awards and Exhibitions as a program aimed at celebrating excellence in Cooperative leadership in Nigeria.   Why govt. needs to collaborate with Cooperatives to diversify economy Cooperatives helping to create jobs, financial inclusion – CFAN Labour ministry plans new registration protocol for cooperatives Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.